text: The Letter Eth comes from the Sumberlandish people In northern Finland to 100 BC to 600 AD the Sumberlandish used "eth" and "ḟ" those 2 letters were a verison of the word "TH" and it used to be called ḟợh and "etợh" ợ was just the two letters "u" and "o" in a word combined it sounded like "oh,cok". ==References== Category:Language
title: Eth (letter)
